<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 EPA proposes to establish time-limited tolerances (with an expiration date of November 15, 1997) for residues of
the synthetic pyrethroid bifenthrin in or on the raw agricultural commodities (RACs) corn (field, seed, and pop)
grain, silage (forage), stover (fodder), milk, milk fat, meat, fat, and meat byproducts of cattle, goats, hogs, horses,
