food use. The Agency is not recommending the establishment of action levels in place of these tolerance regulations.
Since there are no food use registrations associated with these tolerances, exemptions from tolerance, and food
additive regulations, and hence no legal use in the United States, and since these pesticides are either not persistent
or sufficient time has elapsed since their prior use for residues to dissipate, residues should not appear in any domestically
produced commodities.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
